'''Robyn Rihanna Fenty''' {{postnom|list=[[Order of National Heroes|NH]]}}<ref name=NationalHero>{{cite web |title=Barbados National Honours and Decorations 2021 |url=http://governmentprintery.gov.bb/portal/scripts/getpdf.php?i=1583&t=unofficial |publisher=Barbados Government Printing Department |access-date=9 December 2021 |date=1 December 2021 |archive-date=December 4, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211204223132/http://governmentprintery.gov.bb/portal/scripts/getpdf.php?i=1583&t=unofficial |url-status=dead }}</ref> ({{IPAc-en|r|i|ˈ|æ|n|ə|audio=En-us-rihanna.ogg}} {{Respell|ree|ANN|ə}};<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hJP6q7XzLrQ |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/varchive/youtube/20211221/hJP6q7XzLrQ |archive-date=2021-12-21 |url-status=live|title=Rihanna shows AJ Hammer how to pronounce her name.|work=HLN|via=YouTube|access-date=May 2, 2017}}{{cbignore}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=A$AP Rocky Answers 18 Questions From Rihanna |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3AiDa3ZD20Y |website=YouTube |publisher=GQ|date=August 26, 2020|access-date=February 17, 2022}}</ref>{{refn|It is also common for English-language speakers to pronounce her name {{IPAc-en|r|i|'|a:|n|ə}} {{Respell|ree|AH|nə}}|group=n}} born February 20, 1988) is a Barbadian singer, actress, and businesswoman. Born in [[Saint Michael, Barbados|Saint Michael]] and raised in [[Bridgetown]], Barbados, Rihanna auditioned for American record producer [[Carl Sturken and Evan Rogers|Evan Rogers]] who invited her to the United States to record demo tapes. After signing with [[Def Jam Recordings|Def Jam]] in 2005, she soon gained recognition with the release of her first two studio albums, ''[[Music of the Sun]]'' (2005) and ''[[A Girl like Me (Rihanna album)|A Girl Like Me]]'' (2006), both of which were influenced by [[Caribbean music]] and peaked within the top ten of the US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] chart.

Rihanna's third album, ''[[Good Girl Gone Bad]]'' (2007), incorporated elements of [[dance-pop]] and established her status as a [[sex symbol]] in the music industry. The chart-topping single "[[Umbrella (song)|Umbrella]]" earned Rihanna her first [[Grammy Award]] and catapulted her to global stardom. She continued to mix [[pop music|pop]], [[dance music|dance]], and [[contemporary R&B|R&B]] genres on her next studio albums, ''[[Rated R (Rihanna album)|Rated R]]'' (2009), ''[[Loud (Rihanna album)|Loud]]'' (2010), ''[[Talk That Talk]]'' (2011), and ''[[Unapologetic]]'' (2012), the latter of which became her first ''Billboard'' 200 number one. The albums spawned a string of chart-topping singles, including "[[Rude Boy (Rihanna song)|Rude Boy]]", "[[Only Girl (In the World)]]", "[[What's My Name? (Rihanna song)|What's My Name?]]", "[[S&M (song)|S&M]]", "[[We Found Love]]", "[[Where Have You Been]]" and "[[Diamonds (Rihanna song)|Diamonds]]". Her eighth album, ''[[Anti (album)|Anti]]'' (2016), showcased a new creative control following her departure from Def Jam. It became her second US number one album and featured the chart-topping single "[[Work (Rihanna song)|Work]]". During her musical career, Rihanna has collaborated with many artists, such as [[Drake (musician)|Drake]], [[Britney Spears]], [[Eminem]], [[Jay-Z]], [[Kanye West]], [[Adam Levine]], [[Paul McCartney]], [[Ne-Yo]], and [[Shakira]].

With sales of over 250&nbsp;million records worldwide, Rihanna is the [[List of best-selling music artists|second-best-selling female music artist of all time]]. She has earned [[List of Billboard Hot 100 chart achievements and milestones#Most number-one singles|14 number-ones]] and 31 top-ten singles in the US and 30 top-ten entries in the UK. Her [[List of awards and nominations received by Rihanna|accolades]] include nine [[Grammy Award]]s, 13 [[American Music Awards]] (including the [[American Music Award for Icon|Icon Award]]), 12 [[Billboard Music Awards|''Billboard'' Music Awards]], six ''[[Guinness World Records]]'', and the [[NAACP]]'s [[NAACP Image Award – President's Award|President's Award]]. ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' named her one of the [[Time 100|100 most influential people in the world]] in 2012 and 2018. ''[[Forbes]]'' ranked her among the top ten [[Forbes Celebrity 100|highest-paid celebrities]] in 2012 and 2014. As of 2022, she is the wealthiest female musician, with an estimated net worth of $1.4 billion.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Ibile|first=Fagbo|date=2022-08-06|title=Rihanna Forbes|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/rihanna|url-status=live|access-date=2022-08-06|website=Forbes.com}}</ref><ref name="networth">{{Cite news|last1=Pandey|first1=Manish|last2=Brown|first2=Lindsay|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/newsbeat-58084543|title=Fenty Beauty: How make-up helped Rihanna become a billionaire|work=BBC News|date=August 11, 2021|access-date=August 12, 2021}}</ref>

Aside from music, Rihanna is known for her involvement in humanitarian causes, entrepreneurial ventures, and the fashion industry. She is the founder of the nonprofit organisation [[Clara Lionel Foundation]], cosmetics brand [[Fenty Beauty]], and fashion house [[Fenty (fashion house)|Fenty]] under [[LVMH]]; she is the first black woman to head a luxury brand for LVMH.<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Bryant|first=Kenzie|title=Rihanna Is the First Black Woman to Head a Luxury Brand for LVMH|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/style/2019/05/rihanna-luxury-brand-for-lvmh|access-date=April 11, 2021|magazine=Vanity Fair|date=May 10, 2019|language=en-us}}</ref> Rihanna has also ventured into acting, appearing in major roles in ''[[Battleship (film)|Battleship]]'' (2012), ''[[Home (2015 film)|Home]]'' (2015), ''[[Valerian and the City of a Thousand Planets]]'' (2017), and ''[[Ocean's 8]]'' (2018). She was appointed as an ambassador of education, tourism, and investment by the [[Government of Barbados]] in 2018, and was declared a [[National Hero of Barbados]] on the first day of the [[Republicanism in Barbados|country's parliamentary republic]] in 2021, entitling her to the style of "[[The Right Excellent]]" for life.<ref name=NationalHero /> Rihanna will be headlining the [[Super Bowl halftime show|halftime show]] for [[Super Bowl LVII]] on February 12, 2023.
